  "prompt": "How can I play DLC on PS4 disc based games?",
  "response": "To play DLC (Downloadable Content) on PS4 disc-based games, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Install the Game**: Insert the game disc into your PS4 and install the game if it\u2019s not already installed.\n\n2. **Access PlayStation Store**:\n    - From your main menu, navigate to the PlayStation Store and select it.\n    \n3. **Search for the Game**:\n    - Use the search bar in the PlayStation Store to find your game. You can simply type the name of the game to locate it.\n\n4. **Locate DLC**:\n    - Once you\u2019ve found your game, look for the available DLC or add-ons. This is usually listed under the game\u2019s main page in the PlayStation Store.\n\n5. **Buy or Download**:\n    - If the DLC is free, you can simply select download. If it\u2019s a paid DLC, you\u2019ll need to purchase it first. Follow the prompts to complete the purchase and download the content to your PS4.\n\n6. **Download and Install**:\n    - After purchasing, the DLC should start downloading automatically. If not, you can go to your Library > Purchased section to find and download it.\n    - Ensure the DLC is properly installed. The system will usually install it once the download completes, but you may need to check the game to ensure it\u2019s recognized and installed.\n\n7. **Update the Game**:\n    - Make sure your game is up to date. The DLC might require the latest version of the game. Go to Library, select the game, press the Options button, and choose \"Check for Update.\"\n\n8. **Start the Game**:\n    - Load your game from the disc and the new content should be integrated into your game experience.\n\nRemember, you need sufficient storage space on your PS4 hard drive to install DLC. Also, some DLC might not appear in-game until you've reached a certain point or met specific conditions within the game.\n\nFollowing these steps should allow you to enjoy additional content and enhancements in your disc-based PS4 games.",
